author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: After a gunman killed schoolchildren and a teacher in Scotland in 1996, the UK banned handguns; no school shootings have taken place there since.
headline: No School Shootings in the United Kingdom Since Handguns Were Banned?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The gunman suspected of killing at least seventeen people at a school in Florida in February 2018 was a registered Democrat.
headline: Was the Florida School Shooter a Registered Democrat?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: An Instagram account linked to suspected shooter Nikolas Cruz featured an avatar that included a "MAGA" hat.
headline: Did the Florida Shooter’s Instagram Profile Picture Feature a ‘MAGA’ Hat?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: President Trump signed a bill blocking Obama-era background checks on guns for people with mental illnesses.
headline: Did President Trump Revoke Gun Background Checks for Mentally Ill People?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A photograph shows Florida school shooter Nikolas Cruz wearing an antifa t-shirt.
headline: Is This the Florida Shooter in an Antifa Shirt?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The accused school shooter in Florida is a Dreamer, a DACA recipient, or undocumented.
headline: Is the Florida High School Shooter a ‘Dreamer’?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A video shows Muslim migrants destroying a car in Italy.
headline: Did Migrants Destroy a Car in Italy?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The official portrait of former President Barack Obama contains secretly-placed images of sperm cells, including one on his forehead.
headline: Does Barack Obama’s Official Portrait Contain Secret Images of Sperm?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Vice President Mike Pence said that White House aide Rob Porter's purported domestic abuse was supported by the Bible.
headline: Did Mike Pence Defend Rob Porter’s Domestic Abuse with a Bible Verse?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: An image shows Nancy Pelosi's mansion in San Francisco and the large wall that protects the estate.
headline: Is This a Wall Around Nancy Pelosi’s Home?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Hillary Clinton said several insulting things about Michelle Obama in a leaked 20 October 2016 e-mail.							See Example( s )
description: An online image falsely claimed Hillary Clinton insulted the First Lady in an e-mail message purportedly published by WikiLeaks.
headline: FLOTUS Fracas

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The missiles displayed during a North Korean military parade were fake.
description: Although something may have appeared odd about weapons seen during a North Korean military parade, the claim that the country's missiles are fake is only speculation.
headline: Did North Korea Display Fake Missiles During a Military Parade?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Due to a recent court ruling, It is now legal for women in the U.S. to display their breasts in public.
description: Reports that women in the U.S. can now go topless anywhere without fear of legal reprisal are not accurate.
headline: Did a U.S. Federal Court Rule That Women are Free to Display Their Breasts in Public?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Greg Comer is battling cancer.
description: A prayer chain for Comer was reposted in April 2017, more than six years after his death.
headline: Is Greg Comer Battling Cancer?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Michelle Obama filed for divorce after discovering former President Barack Obama had a pregnant mistress.
description: A hoax news site used an old British tabloid photograph to claim that the former First Lady of the United States filed for divorce because her husband impregnated his mistress.
headline: Did Michelle Obama File for Divorce over President Obama's Pregnant Mistress?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Donald Trump donated Play-Doh brand modeling clay to Louisiana flood victims.
description: Presidential candidate Donald Trump was criticized for donating Play-Doh to flood victims in need of food and water, but that wasn't the only item among his donations.
headline: Donald Trump Donated Play-Doh, Other Items to Louisiana Flood Victims?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A photograph shows two women holding anti-Father's Day signs in protest of that day's designation.
description: A photograph that shows two women protesting the observance of Father's Day is a digitally manipulated image.
headline: Protests Seek to #EndFathersDay?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Floyd Mayweather (or Manny Pacquiao) donated a sizable sum of money to Hurricane Harvey relief efforts.
description: A site posing as the Houston Chronicle claimed Mayweather was giving aid money to Hurricane Harvey victims, then a version about Manny Pacquiao surfaced.
headline: Floyd Mayweather Jr. Donates a Whopping Sum of Money to Houston After Hurricane?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The 1987 film Back to the Future II correctly predicted that the Florida Marlins would win the 1997 World Series and that the Cubs would play Florida in the 2015 World Series.							See Example( s )
description: The 1989 film 'Back to the Future II' did not correctly predict Chicago would be the winner of a 2015 Cubs-Marlins World Series match-up.
headline: Future Perfect

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Individuals fleeing danger can request to be "unlisted" in a hotel so no one can find them.							See Example( s )
description: An internet rumor suggested that registering as "unlisted" in a hotel made guests "untouchable," but we couldn't find evidence of any such universal policy.
headline: No Tell Hotel

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: People traveling to the United States under the Visa Waiver Program could be turned away due to new requirements involving biometric passports, or ePassports.							See Example( s )
description: Under Department of Homeland Security guidelines implemented in April 2016, some visitors to the U.S. could be denied entry without biometric passports.
headline: Visa Wavering

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A woman's obituary said that she chose death over the prospect of voting for either Donald Trump or Hillary Clinton.							See Example( s )
description: The obituary of Mary Anne Noland, which said she chose death over the prospect of voting for either Donald Trump or Hillary Clinton, went viral in May 2016.
headline: Clinton, Trump, or Death

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The PGA officially has changed the golf term "a bad lie" to "a Hillary" in honor of Arnold Palmer.
description: A political golf joke involving Arnold Palmer and Hillary Clinton was mistaken for real news by some readers.
headline: A Bad Lie

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Native Americans derisively tagged a pandering U.S. politician with the name Walking Eagle because "he's so full of crap he can't fly."							See Example( s )
description: Joke about Native Americans who derisively tagged a pandering U.S. politician with the name Walking Eagle because 'he's so full of crap he can't fly.'
headline: Walking Eagle

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: An "abortionist" strangled an infant following a failed saline abortion, while other clinicians failed to intervene.							See Example( s )
description: A decades-old story of a doctor purportedly strangling a live infant after complications during a saline abortion was misleadingly shared across social media as news in April 2016.
headline: 'Abortionist Strangles Baby' Facebook Post

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Green Party presidential candidate Dr. Jill Stein has stated that she opposes the use of vaccines.							See Example( s )
description: Dr. Jill Stein's popularity surge during the Democratic National Convention led to rumors that she opposes the use of vaccines.
headline: Jill's Line

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The American Psychiatric Association condones pedophilia and says it is normal to be sexually attracted to children.
description: Blogs dug up an old and misleading article to falsely report that the American Psychiatric Association now condones pedophilia.
headline: Shrink Rap

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Drivers in China commonly intentionally kill pedestrians in hit-and-run accidents.							See Example( s )
description: Do drivers in China commonly intentionally kill pedestrians in hit-and-run accidents?
headline: Chinese Wreckers

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The Dalai Lama described Donald Trump as "worse than Hitler" and a "threat to humanity."
description: His Holiness has offered only superficial commentary about Donald Trump and has not denounced the GOP candidate as "worse than Hitler" or a "threat to humanity."
headline: Dalai Shot

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Russian television host Dmitry Kiselyov exposed a plot to kill Donald Trump
description: Infowars says Putin's "chief propagandist" exposed a plan to take out the GOP presidential nominee, but the report actually cited an op-ed questioning whether Trump was in danger.
headline: From Russia with Trump

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Donald Trump said he would not accept the $400,000 annual president's salary if elected.
description: Donald Trump said in 2015 that he would refuse the $400,000 annual president's salary if elected.
headline: No Pay to Play

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A San Francisco tech company is a front for the web site that accused Julian Assange of pedophilia.
description: A software start-up has been accused of framing the WikiLeaks founder, but the CEO says confusion stemmed from an address mix-up.
headline: False Premise

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Yosemite Sam has been banned from television because his use of guns is offensive and a poor influence on children.							See Example( s )
description: A Facebook meme falsely claims the Looney Tunes character Yosemite Sam has been banned from television due to his use of guns and violence.
headline: Yosemite Scam

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Moderator Chris Wallace received a "cease and desist" letter from Trump about groping allegations in the midst of a presidential debate.
description: A report that moderator Chris Wallace received a legal warning from Trump not to mention groping incidents in the midst of the third presidential debate was satire.
headline: Later, Moderator

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Michelle Obama urged Kansas schoolchildren to "monitor their grandparents for racial intolerance."
description: The First Lady gave a 2014 speech in Topeka commemorating Brown v. Board of Education but did not urge students engage in "KGB-style" enforcement of racial tolerance.
headline: Race Conflating

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Hillary Clinton cancelled a campaign event because of "bizarre eye movements."
description: Hillary Clinton cancelled a North Carolina event due to "changes" to her schedule, but not because of reported "bizarre eye movements."
headline: Eyes Wide Crossed

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: President Obama demanded a monument to himself because "there's plenty of monuments dedicated to racist white people."
description: A conservative site falsely claimed President Obama demanded a monument to himself because "there's plenty of monuments dedicated to racist white people."
headline: A Monumental Lie

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Mylan CEO Heather Bresch donated a large sum of money to the Clinton Foundation.
description: The pharmaceutical company Mylan (manufacturer of the EpiPen), not their CEO personally, donated money to the Clinton Foundation.
headline: Heathers

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Schools in Kent, Washington, have removed pork from school menus because Muslim families were offended.							See Example( s )
description: Schools in Kent, Washington, have long since reduced the amount of pork offered on school menus for reasons unrelated to recent complaints by Muslims.
headline: Pork Chopped

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The Reverend Billy Graham issued a surprising statement in support of Donald Trump.
description: A viral rumor misattributed commentary about choosing between Hillary Clinton and Donald Trump from Franklin Graham to his father, Billy Graham.
headline: Graham Jacker

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: An Australian military veteran single-handedly beat up eight Muslim men who attacked his wife.							See Example( s )
description: The circumstances around a reported January 2016 scuffle on an Australian beach remain unclear.
headline: Aussie Punch

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A Muslim woman entered a co-ed hair salon and demanded all the men there leave so she could take off her veil to get her hair done.
description: A Norwegian hairdresser is facing legal punishment for discriminating against a hijab-wearing woman.
headline: Hijab Dye Job

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Pope Francis decreed that Catholics cannot vote for Democratic presidential candidate Hillary Clinton.							See Example( s )
description: Neither Pope Francis nor any other pope decreed that Catholics cannot vote for Democratic presidential candidate Hillary Clinton.
headline: Franciscan Bunk

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Donald Trump attended a hate group gathering "snubbed" by former GOP candidates Mitt Romney and John McCain.
description: Donald Trump did attend the 2016 Values Voter summit, but the claim that the event was "shunned" by preceding GOP candidates is unfounded.
headline: Trump Stump

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Michael Kors uses fur from dogs that were skinned alive in manufacturing the brand's products.							See Example( s )
description: A since-deleted petition falsely accused the Michael Kors  brand of making items out of fur from dogs that were "skinned alive."
headline: Barkin' Bag

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A photograph shows a man with the word "Trump" tattooed across his forehead.
description: A photograph of a man with the word "Trump" tattooed on his forehead is an old April Fool's joke.
headline: Head Start

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Minecraft has a newly-discovered "sex mod" of which parents should be aware and exercise caution (or restrict the game from their children entirely).
description: Parental pearl-clutching about Minecraft "sex mods" is largely based on misinformation about the popular game.
headline: Parental Misguidance

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Satellite images of hexagon-shaped holes in clouds above the Bermuda Triangle prove that large blasts of sinking air are the cause of mysterious shipwrecks and plane crashes in the area.
description: A perfect storm of sensationalist, ratings-driven science TV, and extremely lazy click-driven journalism resulted in a viral story that explains literally nothing about the “Bermuda Triangle”.
headline: The Bermuda Hexagon

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: 6,000 Muslim migrants with forged papers were captured trying to cross the U.S.-Mexico border.
description: A claim that 6,000 Muslim migrants were captured at the U.S.-Mexico border with forged papers is unsubstantiated.
headline: Border Cajole

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The Supreme Court has upheld former Vice President Dick Cheney's sentence of 20 years in prison on charges related to war crimes.							See Example( s )
description: The Huffington Post published a satirical item set in the future about Dick Cheney's being sentenced to 20 years in prison for war crimes, confusing some readers.
headline: Dick (Ball and) Cheney

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Hillary Clinton's campaign manager Robby Mook deleted most of his tweets due to an FBI investigation.							See Example( s )
description: A disreputable web site spread a baseless rumor holding that Hillary Clinton's campaign manager Robby Mook deleted all of of his tweets because he was "spooked" by an FBI investigation.
headline: Mook Spooked

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: 40 million Russians conducted drills for an imminent nuclear strike.							See Example( s )
description: The drills were part of a disaster exercise, not an indication of an imminent nuclear war.
headline: The Russians Are... Just Practicing

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Dogs and wolves are genetically 99.9% identical.
description: Domestic dogs split from their wild counterpart, the grey wolf, quite recently by evolutionary timescales. As such, the two animals are remarkably similar from a genetic standpoint.
headline: Never Cry Doge

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A picture of a man with his head split open documents the effect of marijuana use.							See Example( s )
description: A picture circulating online uses a picture of actor Steven Yeun while advising, "Say no to drugs, people."
headline: The Walking Pothead

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: An image shows a Muslim child bride in Germany, proving Germany is submitting to "Sharia law."
description: There is no proof an image showing a white-clad little girl is a "child bride," or that Germany is allowing children to marry in accordance with supposed Sharia law.
headline: Bridal Tales

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Marijuana legalization has led to an increase in crime and fatalities all over Colorado.							See Example( s )
description: Denver District Attorney Mitchell Morrissey published a letter painting a bleak picture of marijuana for an anti-legalization campaign.
headline: Rocky Mountain Reefer Madness

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A groundbreaking study showing that algae can draw an alternative source of energy from other plants suggests that humans might be able to draw energy from each other in a similar way.							See Example( s )
description: Viral claims about humans’ ability to sense and feed off of one another’s emotional energy are the result of a comically tortured reading of a groundbreaking study about algae.
headline: Metaphysical Metabolism

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Hillary Clinton refused to exit her vehicle at an event in Florida after the crowd started chanting "lock her up."
description: A Facebook post claiming that Hillary Clinton had cancelled a campaign event due to chants of "lock her up" was shared as genuine news.
headline: Shut Her Up?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Drummer Ginger Baker sodomized a burglar with his cane after catching him in his house.
description: A story that drummer Ginger Baker sodomized a hapless burglar with his cane came from a satirical web site.
headline: Moonshine of Your Love

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The NYPD is investigating and building a case against Bill Clinton pertaining to an underage sex ring.
description: A fake news site seized upon news of an FBI investigation to falsely claim Bill Clinton was implicated in an underage sex ring.
headline: Ring of Untruth

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A list cites instances proving voter fraud in the 2012 U.S. presidential election.							See Example( s )
description: A list of instances supposedly proving voter fraud in the 2012 U.S. presidential election only demonstrates that some people are really bad at math.
headline: 2012 Voter Fraud

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Hillary Clinton is disqualified from holding the office of President under the provisions of U.S. Code Title 18, Section 2071.							See Example( s )
description: A chain message claims that Hillary Clinton is disqualified from holding public office under U.S. Code Title 18, Section 2071, but the application of that law to her is doubtful.
headline: Don't Forget to Strip Your Server

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The Amish Brotherhood have endorsed Donald Trump for president.
description: A hoax news article reported that "millions" of Amish people were throwing their support behind Donald Trump in the 2016 presidential election.
headline: Amish Wish

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Chattanooga-area NBC affiliate WRCB inadvertently exposed the rigging of 2016 election results in Hillary Clinton's favor.							See Example( s )
description: In what is becoming a common pre-election conspiracy-driving glitch, an NBC affiliate's software test was interpreted as evidence election results were rigged.
headline: The Fix's Din

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Al Capone said that the United States wouldn't elect a woman president until the Chicago Cubs won the World Series.							See Example( s )
description: A quote ostensibly uttered by notorious gangster Al Capone about electing a woman president when the Chicago Cubs win the World Series is fake.
headline: Cubs Win, the Woman's In

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A van full of "illegals" traveled from voting booth to voting booth in Arizona in order to vote (illegally) for Hillary Clinton.
description: Fake "voter fraud" stories showed up early and often during 2016's general election.
headline: Voter Van

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: BBC's Carol Kirkwood used a curse word to describe the weather.							See Example( s )
description: Reports that that BBC's Carol Kirkwood used a curse word to describe the weather are fake news.
headline: Scold Outside

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A list of 'Which Side of the Fence?' entries originated with comedian Jeff Foxworthy.							See Example( s )
description: Did a list of 'Which Side of the Fence' entries originate with comedian Jeff Foxworthy?
headline: Which Side of the Fence?

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Former Monty Python member John Cleese penned a satirical piece announcing the revocation of America's independence for failure to elect a competent president.							See Example( s )
description: Former Monty Python member John Cleese did not pen a satirical piece announcing the revocation of America's independence for failure to elect a competent president.
headline: Revocation of Independence

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A woman set her husband on fire for molesting their daughter.
description: An genuine news story from 2014 is often shared along with a series of unrelated images.
headline: You're Fired

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Anti-Trump protesters beat a homeless veteran to death in Philadelphia.							See Example( s )
description: A video allegedly showing anti-Trump protesters beating a man to death in Philadelphia was actually filmed in 2015 and is unrelated to the protests.
headline: Instant Repay

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A Harvard Study showed that Tibetan Monks can significantly raise the temperature of their fingers, toes and other extremities through meditation alone.
description: A 1982 study of Tibetan practitioners of "g-tummo" yoga did indeed demonstrate their ability to raise the temperature of different parts of their body.
headline: Monk-y Business

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Donald Trump announced plans to convert the USS Enterprise into a "floating hotel and casino."							See Example( s )
description: A story  that Donald Trump was planning to "repurpose" the USS Enterprise was just another piece of military satire.
headline: Trump Taj Mah-Hull

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Celebrity Cruise lines released an ad saying that Donald Trump's supporters were no longer welcome on their ships.
description: Celebrity Cruise Lines released an advertisement addressing some of Donald Trump's talking points from the 2016 presidential election, but they did not say that his supporters were not welcome.
headline: Beyond Borders

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A majority of anti-Trump protesters did not vote in the 2016 general election.							See Example( s )
description: Articles and rumors claimed that a majority of anti-Trump demonstrators did not vote in the very election they protested.
headline: Boo, Don't Vote

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A Mexican supermarket chain is adding "donations" for a U.S.-Mexico border wall to its charges.							See Example( s )
description: A faked photograph led to accusations that Soriana markets were making customers foot the bill for one of Donald Trump's campaign promises.
headline: Mercado de Supermentiras

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A Rutgers University professor was forced into a psychological evaluation due to political tweets.
description: Kevin Allred, who teaches women's and gender studies at Rutgers, said his First Amendment rights were violated when police detained him for a rhetorical tweet about shooting white people.
headline: Psyche War

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: An FBI agent investigating Hillary Clinton's use of a private e-mail server killed himself after murdering his wife.
description: Reports that an FBI agent investigating Hillary Clinton's use of a private e-mail server killed himself after murdering his wife are just fake news.
headline: FBI Agent Suspected in Hillary Email Leaks Found Dead

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Shoplifter who attempts to conceal a chicken under her hat is caught when the frozen loot renders her unconscious.							See Example( s )
description: Did a shoplifter who stashed a frozen chicken under her hat die of 'frozen brain'?
headline: The Meathead

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A phone number posted on a "consumer watchdog" site belongs to a college loan servicer.							See Example( s )
description: We called "EDU Loan Servicing" after it was featured on a "consumer watchdog" page; it appears to be one of many scams.
headline: Wrong Number

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A woman pulled a Muslim woman's hijab inside a Walmart and told her, "Go hang yourself with it around your neck."							See Example( s )
description: A woman's uncorroborated Facebook post describing the alleged incident was shared thousands of times.
headline: Islamophobia on Aisle Five

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Jellyfish and lobsters are considered biologically immortal, meaning they don’t age and will never die unless they are killed.							See Example( s )
description: Some jellyfish do meet the definition of biologic immortality, but lobsters do not make the cut.
headline: Mortality, Actually

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: President Barack Obama signed an executive order banning all fake news outlets.
description: A story that the President is banning all fake news came from — you guessed it — a fake news site.
headline: Execu-Fib Order

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Jill Stein was arrested and charged with embezzling money raised for 2016 recount efforts in order to throw a "marijuana dinner party."							See Example( s )
description: An old photograph of Jill Stein was used to claim that the Green Party presidential candidate had been arrested for using "recount funds" to host a "marijuana dinner party."
headline: The Green Party's Green Party

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Donald Trump promised on Twitter that his first act as president would be to pardon Dylann Roof.
description: An image purporting to show a tweet sent by Donald Trump, in which he promised to pardon accused mass shooter Dylann Roof, was a hoax.
headline: Dylann Proof

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The Communist Party of the USA endorsed Hillary Clinton.							See Example( s )
description: The Communist Party of the USA did not endorse Hillary Clinton, but did encourage members to vote against her rival, Donald Trump.
headline: Party Pooper

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A woman's IQ skyrocketed to an historic 220 after she drank sperm or semen for a year.							See Example( s )
description: A stolen screenshot was attached to a fake story about the amazing cognitive benefits of "drinking sperm."
headline: Sperm Whale

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: A document held by a potential Trump cabinet member reveals his immigration plans.
description: While one of Trump's potential cabinet picks unwittingly revealed his harsh immigration proposals, it is inaccurate to claim it's Trump's plan.
headline: Bleak Peak

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: The Dakota Access Pipeline (DAPL) was re-routed through the Standing Rock Reservation after Bismarck's mostly-white residents refused to allow it near their water supply.							See Example( s )
description: As disputes and protests over the Dakota Access Pipeline continued, rumors appeared that the pipeline was re-routed after residents of Bismarck refused the risk.
headline: Mind Your Own Bismarck

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Clint Eastwood refused to accept the Presidential Medal of Freedom from President Obama.
description: A rumor that Clint Eastwood was offered — and refused — the Presidential Medal of Freedom was made up out of whole cloth.
headline: The Man With No Award

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Trump arranged a deal with Carrier that kept a thousand jobs in the United States.  							See Example( s )
description: A widely-reported deal arranged by the President-elect with Carrier kept 1,000 jobs in the U.S., according to both parties.
headline: Air Conditions

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Apple's purge of "fake news" apps from the App store started with the removal of Breitbart News in November 2016.							See Example( s )
description: Rumors circulated that Apple was purging its app store of "fake news" web sites — starting with Breitbart's news app.
headline: Cen-Store-Ship

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Republicans in Texas made significant cuts to Medicaid after they were "emboldened" by the results of the 2016 general election.							See Example( s )
description: A viral article inaccurately reported that Medicaid spending cuts in Texas affecting disabled children were thanks to "emboldened" state Republicans.
headline: Texan Beef

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Sarah Palin called for a Mall of America boycott over its hiring a black man to play Santa Claus.							See Example( s )
description: A story that the former Alaska governor called for the boycott after discovering that the mall had hired its first black Santa Claus is a hoax.
headline: Santa Laws

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Donald Trump selected Mexican drug lord El Chapo to head the Drug Enforcement Administration.							See Example( s )
description: A report that Donald Trump tapped El Chapo as head of the Drug Enforcement Administration originated from a well-known humor columnist.
headline: Cartel of the Ball

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Police opened fire on a store mannequin after it failed to follow their orders.							See Example( s )
description: Police in Scranton, Pennsylvania, did not gun down a store mannequin that "failed to comply" with their orders.
headline: Blast Test Dummy

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Backless boosters will be banned in the United States starting in December 2016.							See Example( s )
description: A social media meme shared outdated information about the use of backless booster seats (also known as booster cushions).
headline: Booster Ban

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Article details efforts of John Glenn's wife to overcome stuttering.							See Example( s )
description: How John Glenn's wife, Annie, overcame her stuttering.
headline: Annie Glenn

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Secretary of State John Kerry "funneled" taxpayer money into his daughter's global charity.
description: Dr. Vanessa Kerry's nonprofit organization, Seed Global Health, was awarded Peace Corps funding before and after her father, John Kerry, became U.S. Secretary of State; was there a conflict of interest?
headline: Cash & Kerry

author.properties.name: Snopes
claimReviewed: Nordstrom sells a rock in a leather pouch for $85, and a smaller version for $65.							See Example( s )
description: Nordstrom really is selling a rock in a leather pouch for $85 (and a smaller version for $65 for the cost conscious).
headline: Rock, Paper, Blither
